      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DON CRUNCH (7) resumes from a spell of 11 weeks after closing off last campaign in good form, scoring at his last appearance over 2190m at Mildura. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position. Likely to run a big race to kick off this campaign. BIGBASHASH (6) finished fourth last start, beaten 14 metres at Horsham over 1700m. Talented and has plenty of upside. Has ability and should be right in the finish. FIVE CENT (4) didn't do a bad job when sixth over 1690m at Maryborough last time out. Has top-three claims. RAVISHING ROXY (3) won two runs back then her luck changed last time when she broke and finished 5.5 metres back in fifth over 1609m at this track. No excuses from this advantageous draw. Only needs to get things right to be in the money.",
